comments.body:
I'd recommend avoid using `curValue` whenever is possible.. it's an internal property, not even documented and so might change without further notice.

if `.get()` cannot be used because it will add a reactivity/computation, you can use `Tracker.nonreactive`:

```suggestion
	this.onSelectAgents = Tracker.nonreactive(({ item: agent }) => {
		const selectedAgents = this.selectedAgents.get();
		selectedAgents.push(agent);
		this.selectedAgents.set(selectedAgents);
	});

diffHunk:
@@ -1,1 +180,184 @@	this.selectedAgents = new ReactiveVar([]);

	this.onSelectAgents = ({ item: agent }) => {
		this.selectedAgents.set([agent]);
	};
